# Node.js Architecture

We are using Node.js for our backend application.

## Framework Architecture
<% if (options.architecture === 'nestjs') { %>
- **CRITICAL**: We are using **NestJS**.
- Follow strict Angular-style modular architecture.
- Group related features into self-contained `Modules`.
- All business logic must live inside `@Injectable()` Services.
- Controllers should only handle HTTP requests and responses, delegating logic to services.
- Always use Dependency Injection (DI) via the constructor.
<% } else if (options.architecture === 'express') { %>
- We are using **Express.js**.
- Follow a standard Model-View-Controller (MVC) or Route-Controller-Service pattern.
- Keep route definitions separate from controller logic.
- Place all business logic inside dedicated Service files rather than inside the Express route handlers.
- Use middleware for cross-cutting concerns like authentication and validation.
<% } else { %>
- Follow standard Node.js architectural patterns.
<% } %>

## General Node.js Rules
- This is a backend service. Never write browser-specific code (e.g., `window` or `document`).
- Always handle async errors properly (try/catch or async middleware wrappers) to prevent unhandled promise rejections.
